{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17651081","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17651081"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:21:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:21:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18434"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18434","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18434"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11152"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74698"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11152","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11152"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18434"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60181"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"5395"},{"type":"tags","id":"7707"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25857"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25863"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74698","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74698"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA research team is studying whether a new exercise program affects blood pressure in patients with hypertension. They randomly assign participants to either the exercise program or usual care.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following represents the dependent variable in this study?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Number of participants","Patient age at enrollment","Duration of study participation","Exercise program assignment","Blood pressure measurements"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eblood pressure measurements\u003C/strong\u003E represent the dependent variable because this is the outcome that is expected to change in response to the intervention (exercise program). The dependent variable is what researchers measure to determine if the intervention had an effect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExercise program assignment\u003C/strong\u003E is the independent variable - it is controlled by the researchers and is not dependent on other factors\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuration of study participation \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003Enumber of participants\u003C/strong\u003E are study parameters that are predetermined and not outcomes being measured\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPatient age at enrollment\u003C/strong\u003E is a demographic characteristic that cannot be influenced by the intervention.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn experimental research, the dependent variable must be something that can be measured and is expected to respond to changes in the independent variable. The relationship between these variables forms the basis for statistical analysis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A dependent variable is the outcome or response that changes based on the independent variable being tested.","In clinical research, dependent variables are typically measurable health outcomes like blood pressure, survival time, or symptom scores.","The dependent variable must be clearly defined and measurable to allow for statistical analysis."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60181"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18434"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60181","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60181"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-26T15:52:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-26T15:52:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11152"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74698"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","synonyms":null,"description":"Understand (interpreting and summarizing information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4948","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4948"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udcca","name":"Biostatistics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T13:30:29+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"